@startuml Sequence_RealtimeInApp
title Feature 10 - Real-Time In-App Notification Delivery

participant "InAppChannel" as Channel
database "PostgreSQL" as DB
participant "Redis\nPub/Sub" as Redis
participant "Next.js SSE\nEndpoint" as SSE
participant "Browser\nEventSource" as ES
participant "useNotifications\nHook" as Hook
participant "Notification\nCenter UI" as UI

note over ES, SSE
    Browser connects to SSE on page load:
    new EventSource('/api/events')
end note

ES -> SSE : GET /api/events\n(long-lived connection)
SSE -> Redis : SUBSCRIBE\nuser:{userId}:notifications

... Event occurs (e.g., price increase detected) ...

Channel -> Redis : PUBLISH\nuser:{userId}:notifications\n{ type: 'notification.created',\n  notification: { ... } }

Redis --> SSE : Message received
SSE --> ES : data: { type:\n'notification.created',\nnotification: { id, title,\nbody, severity } }

ES -> Hook : onMessage callback
Hook -> Hook : Prepend notification\nto local cache
Hook -> Hook : Increment\nunreadCount

Hook -> UI : Re-render
UI -> UI : Show unread badge\n(orange dot on bell icon)
UI -> UI : If notification center open,\nshow new item at top

note right of UI
    User taps notification
end note

UI -> Hook : markAsRead(notifId)
Hook -> DB : UPDATE notifications\nSET read=true, read_at=now()
Hook -> Hook : Decrement unreadCount
Hook -> UI : Update badge count

@enduml
